# Go via `dev` container

This repo does not assume `go` on the host PATH. **Always** run Go through the **`dev`** service in [`docker-compose.yml`](docker-compose.yml) (Go 1.22, project mounted at `/src`).

## Commands

From the repository root:

```bash
docker compose run --rm dev go test ./...
docker compose run --rm dev go build -o sage .
docker compose run --rm dev go mod tidy
```

Prefer Makefile wrappers when they match the task: `make test`, `make build`, `make tidy`.

For non-interactive agent/CI runs, set `SAGE_NO_TTY=1` on compose invocations if TTY allocation causes issues.

## Do not

- Run bare `go test`, `go build`, `go mod`, etc. on the host.
- Assume a local Go version matches the project (use the container).

## Contract tests

CLI tests in [`cmd/cli_contract_test.go`](cmd/cli_contract_test.go) build and invoke the `sage` binary via subprocess. Run the full suite with `make test` or `docker compose run --rm dev go test ./...`.
